@startuml
title PROCESS STEWARD - Detailed Sequence (Lite Agentic Dev)\nDocument-driven + Gates + Loops + CCR (ASCII-safe)\nGates must match process/PROGRESS.md (G0..G5)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
skinparam SequenceLifeLineBorderColor #333333
skinparam SequenceParticipantBorderColor #333333
skinparam SequenceParticipantFontColor #111111
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFF9D6
skinparam NoteBorderColor #333333
skinparam ParticipantPadding 25
skinparam BoxPadding 10

actor Human
participant Agent
database RepoFS as "Repo/FS"
participant CI
participant Cloud

note over Human,Agent
Truth sources (files in repo):
- product/PRD.md      : scope truth (stories S-V###, acceptance, DoD, sequence; optional UC tags)
- process/PROGRESS.md : state truth (trackers, evidence, decisions, policy, CCR log)
- product/ARCH.md     : architecture truth (approval-controlled; RO during build P5-P7)
- product/contracts/* : executable contracts (RO during build unless CCR approved)
Verifier (deterministic):
- `make check` runs lint/typecheck/tests (and contract validation if enabled)
end note

loop VERSION LIFECYCLE (MVP -> V1.1 -> V2 ...)
  Agent -> RepoFS: READ process/PROGRESS.md (current_version, gates, policy)
  Agent -> RepoFS: READ product/PRD.md (roadmap, scope, story sequence)

  alt First run OR no current_version
    Agent -> RepoFS: SET PROGRESS.current_version = MVP
    Agent -> RepoFS: INIT gates G0..G5 = PENDING
    Agent -> RepoFS: WRITE process/PROGRESS.md
    Agent --> Human: PROMPT "Confirm version label MVP (or provide another)"
    Human --> Agent: RESP "OK" (or provide version id)
  else Next version
    Agent --> Human: PROMPT "Proceed with next version? Provide version id or STOP"
    Human --> Agent: RESP (e.g., V1.1) OR STOP
    alt STOP
      break
    else Continue
      Agent -> RepoFS: UPDATE PROGRESS.current_version = <new version>
      Agent -> RepoFS: RESET phase/gate statuses for version
      Agent -> RepoFS: WRITE process/PROGRESS.md
    end
  end

  ' ---------------------------
  ' P0 INSTALL AND WIRE
  ' ---------------------------
  group P0 INSTALL AND WIRE (Setup)
    Agent -> RepoFS: VERIFY required artifacts exist (process/*, product/*, Makefile, pyproject.toml)
    alt Missing artifacts
      Agent --> Human: PROMPT "Missing artifacts detected. Approve creation of templates?"
      Human --> Agent: APPROVE
      Agent -> RepoFS: CREATE missing templates (minimal)
    end

    Agent -> CI: RUN `make check` (baseline wiring validation)
    CI --> Agent: RESULT pass/fail + diagnostics + evidence

    alt `make check` FAIL
      loop Verification loop (setup fixes)
        Agent -> RepoFS: APPLY wiring/config fixes based on diagnostics
        Agent -> CI: RUN `make check`
        CI --> Agent: RESULT pass/fail + evidence
      end
    end

    Agent -> RepoFS: WRITE process/PROGRESS.md (G0 = PASS: Installed (artifacts exist + check runnable) + evidence)
    Agent --> Human: NOTICE "G0 PASS: Installed (artifacts exist + check runnable)"
  end

  ' ---------------------------
  ' P1-P4 READY TO BUILD
  ' ---------------------------
  group P1-P4 READY TO BUILD (Scope, Architecture, Contracts, Policy)
    ' P1 Functional framing: agent can propose PRD from vision-only seed
    Agent -> RepoFS: READ product/PRD.md (vision + seed)
    Agent -> RepoFS: DRAFT missing PRD sections (S-V###, acceptance/DoD, sequence, optional UC tags)
    Agent --> Human: PROMPT "Approve PRD scope (stories S-V###, acceptance/DoD, sequence; optional UC tags). Stories must be vertical slices deliverable in <=1 day."
    alt Human EDIT
      Human --> Agent: EDITS (patch/notes)
      Agent -> RepoFS: APPLY patch to product/PRD.md
      Agent -> RepoFS: WRITE process/PROGRESS.md (decisions/questions logged)
      Agent --> Human: PROMPT "Re-approve updated PRD scope"
      Human --> Agent: APPROVE
    else Human REJECT
      Human --> Agent: REJECT reasons
      loop Rework scope until approved
        Agent -> RepoFS: REVISE product/PRD.md proposal
        Agent --> Human: PROMPT "Approve revised PRD scope"
        Human --> Agent: APPROVE or EDIT
      end
    else Human APPROVE
      Human --> Agent: APPROVE
    end
    Agent -> RepoFS: WRITE process/PROGRESS.md (G1 = PASS: Scope approved (PRD accepted))

    ' P2 Architecture (approval-controlled)
    Agent -> RepoFS: PROPOSE updates to product/ARCH.md (repo map, conventions, boundaries, extension points)
    Agent --> Human: PROMPT "Approve ARCH tradeoffs only (boundaries/conventions/stack). ARCH becomes RO during build."
    alt Human edits
      Human --> Agent: EDITS
      Agent -> RepoFS: APPLY patch to product/ARCH.md
    end
    Agent -> RepoFS: WRITE process/PROGRESS.md (decisions logged)

    ' P3 Contracts baseline (optional but supported by pack)
    Agent -> RepoFS: PROPOSE minimal product/contracts/* baseline (OpenAPI + schemas/types) OR confirm not needed
    Agent --> Human: PROMPT "Enable contracts? If yes, approve baseline semantics (names/fields/errors). If no, confirm 'contracts disabled' policy."
    alt Contracts ENABLED
      Human --> Agent: APPROVE contracts enabled
      Agent -> CI: RUN `make check` (includes contract validation if configured)
      CI --> Agent: RESULT pass/fail + diagnostics + evidence
      alt FAIL
        loop Fix contracts until validate
          Agent -> RepoFS: FIX product/contracts/* per diagnostics
          Agent -> CI: RUN `make check`
          CI --> Agent: RESULT
        end
      end
    else Contracts DISABLED
      Human --> Agent: CONFIRM disabled
      Agent -> RepoFS: UPDATE PROGRESS policy "contracts disabled for this version"
    end

    ' P4 Policy + story baseline
    Agent -> RepoFS: UPDATE process/PROGRESS.md policy (story-level approval; high-risk task review only; CCR rules)
    Agent --> Human: PROMPT "Approve policy (story-level approval, high-risk-only review; CCR required if contracts enabled)"
    alt Human edits policy
      Human --> Agent: EDITS
      Agent -> RepoFS: APPLY policy edits (process/PROGRESS.md)
    end

    Agent -> CI: RUN `make check` (final Ready-to-Build gate)
    CI --> Agent: RESULT pass/fail + evidence
    alt FAIL
      loop Fix pre-build issues until green
        Agent -> RepoFS: FIX (config/contracts/tests) per diagnostics
        Agent -> CI: RUN `make check`
        CI --> Agent: RESULT
      end
    end

    Agent -> RepoFS: WRITE process/PROGRESS.md (G2 = PASS: Ready-to-build (contracts validate + check green) + evidence)
    Agent --> Human: NOTICE "G2 PASS: Ready-to-build (contracts validate + check green)"
  end

  ' ---------------------------
  ' P5-P7 STORY DELIVERY LOOP
  ' ---------------------------
  group P5-P7 STORY DELIVERY (Story loop -> Task loop -> Verification + CCR)
    Agent -> RepoFS: READ product/PRD.md (story sequence + acceptance)
    Agent -> RepoFS: READ process/PROGRESS.md (trackers + policy)

    loop STORY LOOP (for each S-V### in PRD sequence)
      Agent -> RepoFS: MARK Story S-V### = IN_PROGRESS (process/PROGRESS.md)

      ' P5 JIT planning per story
      Agent -> RepoFS: GENERATE JIT task checklist (5-15 tasks T-V###.## + deps + risk)
      Agent -> RepoFS: WRITE process/PROGRESS.md (tasks planned + risk flags)

      alt High-risk tasks exist
        Agent --> Human: PROMPT "Approve HIGH-risk tasks only for this story (T-V###.## set)"
        alt Human edits/rejects
          Human --> Agent: EDITS / REJECT
          Agent -> RepoFS: ADJUST tasks in process/PROGRESS.md
          Agent --> Human: PROMPT "Re-approve high-risk set"
          Human --> Agent: APPROVE
        else Approved
          Human --> Agent: APPROVE
        end
      else No high-risk tasks
        Agent --> Human: FYI "Proceeding with LOW/MED tasks per policy"
      end

      ' P6 Task loop
      loop TASK LOOP (for each T-V###.## in checklist order)
        Agent -> RepoFS: MARK Task T-V###.## = IN_PROGRESS (process/PROGRESS.md)
        Agent -> RepoFS: IMPLEMENT minimal code change + unit tests
        Agent -> CI: RUN `make check`
        CI --> Agent: RESULT pass/fail + diagnostics + evidence
        Agent -> RepoFS: APPEND evidence to process/PROGRESS.md (for this task)

        alt `make check` PASS and no contract issue
          Agent -> RepoFS: MARK Task = DONE (process/PROGRESS.md)
        else `make check` FAIL OR contract mismatch suspected
          alt Contract gap/drift detected AND contracts enabled
            Agent -> RepoFS: CREATE CCR entry (CCR-###) with evidence + minimal proposal
            Agent -> RepoFS: MARK Task = BLOCKED (reason: CCR-###)
            Agent --> Human: PROMPT "CCR decision required: APPROVE/REJECT/DEFER (no workaround)"

            alt CCR APPROVED
              Human --> Agent: APPROVE CCR
              Agent -> RepoFS: UPDATE product/contracts/* (minimal change)
              Agent -> CI: RUN `make check`
              CI --> Agent: RESULT pass/fail
              alt still FAIL
                loop Post-CCR verification fixes
                  Agent -> RepoFS: FIX implementation to match approved contract
                  Agent -> CI: RUN `make check`
                  CI --> Agent: RESULT
                end
              end
              Agent -> RepoFS: MARK CCR = APPLIED+VERIFIED
              Agent -> RepoFS: MARK Task = IN_PROGRESS (resume)
            else CCR REJECTED/DEFERRED
              Human --> Agent: REJECT or DEFER
              Agent -> RepoFS: MARK Task = BLOCKED or CANCELLED (per decision)
              break
            end

          else Non-contract failures (verification loop)
            loop Verification loop (fix until green)
              Agent -> RepoFS: FIX code/tests per diagnostics
              Agent -> CI: RUN `make check`
              CI --> Agent: RESULT pass/fail + evidence
              Agent -> RepoFS: APPEND evidence to process/PROGRESS.md
            end
            Agent -> RepoFS: MARK Task = DONE (process/PROGRESS.md)
          end
        end
      end

      ' P7 Story handshake
      Agent --> Human: PROMPT "Validate story S-V### acceptance (PASS/FAIL + notes)"
      alt Human FAIL
        Human --> Agent: FAIL + feedback
        Agent -> RepoFS: LOG feedback in process/PROGRESS.md
        Agent -> RepoFS: APPLY fixes + tests
        Agent -> CI: RUN `make check`
        CI --> Agent: RESULT
        alt still FAIL
          loop Fix acceptance until green
            Agent -> RepoFS: FIX
            Agent -> CI: RUN `make check`
            CI --> Agent: RESULT
          end
        end
        Agent --> Human: PROMPT "Re-validate acceptance"
        Human --> Agent: PASS
      else Human PASS
        Human --> Agent: PASS
      end

      Agent -> RepoFS: MARK Story = DONE (process/PROGRESS.md)
      Agent -> RepoFS: RECORD G3 evidence for this story (process/PROGRESS.md)
      Agent --> Human: NOTICE "G3 PASS for story: Story done (repeats per story)"
    end
  end

  ' ---------------------------
  ' P8-P12 HARDENING + RELEASE
  ' ---------------------------
  group P8-P12 HARDENING AND RELEASE
    Agent -> CI: RUN hardening (integration/e2e) if enabled by policy
    CI --> Agent: RESULT pass/fail + evidence
    alt FAIL
      loop Fix hardening until green
        Agent -> RepoFS: FIX
        Agent -> CI: RUN hardening stage
        CI --> Agent: RESULT
      end
    end
    Agent -> RepoFS: WRITE process/PROGRESS.md (G4 = PASS: Release candidate (hardening complete))

    Agent -> RepoFS: DRAFT release notes + deploy checklist (process/PROGRESS.md)
    Agent --> Human: PROMPT "Deploy now and confirm outcome"
    Human -> Cloud: DEPLOY (staging/prod)
    Cloud --> Human: DEPLOY RESULT (ok/fail)

    alt Deploy failed
      Human --> Agent: FAIL + logs
      loop Fix and retry deploy
        Agent -> RepoFS: FIX deploy issues
        Agent -> CI: RUN `make check`
        CI --> Agent: RESULT
        Human -> Cloud: RETRY DEPLOY
        Cloud --> Human: RESULT
      end
    else Deploy ok
      Human --> Agent: DEPLOYED_OK + smoke result
    end

    Agent -> RepoFS: WRITE process/PROGRESS.md (G5 = PASS: Released (deployed + smoke + notes))
    Agent --> Human: PROMPT "Provide feedback/telemetry summary for backlog"
    Human --> Agent: Feedback + next priorities
    Agent -> RepoFS: UPDATE product/PRD.md (roadmap candidates) + process/PROGRESS.md (learnings/issues)
  end

end loop

@enduml
